Inform

   With the Pack of the Giant.

Communicate

   Via our website, networks, forums and in the field.

Raise Awareness

   The association takes action in sports clubs and is accompanied by a
   team of professionals.

Listen

   Via our website (private message, blog), Facebook and Twitter page
   (private message), phone line…

   The phrase

   “Colosse aux pieds d’argile” -”the Giant with feet of clay” in English-
   symbolizes a power that seems invulnerable but which is built on a
   fragile base.
   It comes from the interpretation of a dream by the prophet Daniel which
   announced the collapse of the Kingdom of Babylon.

The association in a few words


Who are we?

   “Colosse aux pieds d’argile” is a non-profit association under the
   French law of 1901 founded in 2013 by Sébastien Boueilh.
   Read his story

Our mission

Notre misson

   The mission of the association “Colosse aux pieds d’argile” is to
   prevent and raise awareness about paedophile and hazing risks in sports
   and in all children spheres. Its purpose is to assist and help the
   victims. It is also concerned with the protection of the supervisors
   against any compromising situation.

What we do

   In our actions, we protect the children and all the professional actors
   and volunteers supervising children (coaches, sports instructors, youth
   leaders, volunteers, parents…). We help them identify and assist a
   victim but especially not to put themselves in situations that could be
   misinterpreted.

Who is concerned?

   For all the people supervising children
   For sports clubs (leaders, sports instructors, volunteers)
   For communities
   For licence-holders from 5 to 15 years old
   For parents…

Testimonies

     *

     “Hello and congratulations for your initiative! My children are part
     of a rugby club and I would really like your association to organise
     prevention initiatives for players on this theme still taboo but so
     important for everyone, whether we are victims or not.”
     *

     “Taboos are still too rooted in the society, particularly here! I
     hope the courage of those who created the association will help
     break down taboos and silence! So, I repeat: thank you to the
     Association for being there, finally!”


